Use the standard library
This is how to separate_paren_groups of paren_string:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that current is []
   Remember that n is paren_string's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Remember that open_count is 0
   Remember that is_string is isstring of paren_string
   
   Do this n times:
      Remember that c is item i in paren_string
      
      When is_string, then:
         Remember that code is toint of c
      But, if not:
         Remember that code is c
      End when
      
      When code is 40, then:
         Add current to c
         Increase open_count
      End when
      
      When code is 41, then:
         Add current to c
         Decrease open_count
         
         When open_count is 0, then:
            Add result to current
            Remember that current is []
         End when
      End when
      
      Increase i
   End do
   
   The answer is result
Now you know